# AI change checklist (before finishing)

Answer honestly; if several are **no**, refactor before stopping.

- Did I fix the **root cause**?
- Did I put logic in the **correct layer**?
- Did I **duplicate** interpretation logic?
- Will this **generalize** to nearby variants?
- Is this a **bandaid**?
- Did I preserve the **canonical path**?
- Did I add tests that **prove generalization** (not only the one line that broke)?
